        <h2>Tips</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Be specific.</strong> "Fix the bug" gives Claude nothing to work with. "Fix the bug in <span class="ic">calculateTotal</span> — it returns NaN when the cart is empty" — that works.</li>
          <li><strong>Give context.</strong> Before a code review, describe what the code does. Before debugging, describe what you expected vs. what happened.</li>
          <li><strong>Use it for learning.</strong> Ask Claude to explain decisions: "Why did you use a closure here?" or "What's the trade-off between these two approaches?"</li>
          <li><strong>Chain skills.</strong> Write feature → <span class="ic">/code-review</span> → <span class="ic">/write-tests</span> → <span class="ic">/commit-message</span> → <span class="ic">/pr-description</span>. A complete professional workflow in minutes.</li>
          <li><strong>Review everything.</strong> Claude Code is powerful but not infallible. Read the code before committing — you're the engineer responsible for the outcome.</li>
        </ul>

